# Immich Docker Deployment — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
Self-hosted photo/video management (Google Photos alternative) deployed via Docker Compose.

## Key Files
- `docker-compose.yml` — 4 services: immich-server, immich-machine-learning, redis, database
- `.env` — Environment variables (IMMICH_VERSION, TZ, DB_PASSWORD, UPLOAD_LOCATION)
- `AI/` — Documentation, scripts, and cheat sheets for this deployment

## Core Commands
```bash
# Start (never pull — network issues with ghcr.io in Bolivia)
docker compose up -d --pull never

# Status
docker ps --format 'table {{.Names}}\t{{.Status}}\t{{.Ports}}'

# Logs
docker compose logs -f immich-server

# Stop
docker compose down
```

## Known Issues
- Docker Desktop's internal proxy (`http.docker.internal:3128`) causes TLS handshake timeout
  with `ghcr.io` from Bolivia (high latency). Docker Hub works fine.
- Use `AI/pull-images.py` to download ghcr.io images via direct HTTP API when needed.
- The `docker-compose.yml` has `@sha256:` digests removed to match locally loaded images.

## Configuration
- Web UI: `http://localhost:2283`
- Timezone: `America/La_Paz`
- Photos stored in: `./library/` (never modify manually — use app/web/CLI)
- DB data in: `./postgres/` (never use network shares)

## When Making Changes
- Always test with `docker compose config` before applying
- After image changes, tag with `docker tag <id> ghcr.io/immich-app/<name>:release`
- DO NOT restore `@sha256:` digests in docker-compose.yml — they cause pull failures
- Reference `AI/` folder for context before troubleshooting
- Use `--pull never` flag to prevent Docker from trying to reach ghcr.io

## Services
| Name | Image | Port |
|---|---|---|
| immich_server | ghcr.io/immich-app/immich-server:release | 2283 |
| immich_machine_learning | ghcr.io/immich-app/immich-machine-learning:release | — |
| immich_postgres | ghcr.io/immich-app/postgres:14-vectorchord... | 5432 |
| immich_redis | docker.io/valkey/valkey:9 | 6379 |
